Games Offload (Bind Mount)

Commands executed and verified to work:

# Create destination on /var SSD
sudo mkdir -p /var/games
sudo chown ken:ken /var/games

# Move files safely
rsync -avP /home/ken/games/ /var/games/

# Prepare mount point
mv /home/ken/games /home/ken/games_old
mkdir /home/ken/games

# Update fstab (already reflected above)
# /var/games    /home/ken/games    none    bind    0 0

# Test mount
sudo mount -a
ls /home/ken/games

# Cleanup (after verification)
rm -rf /home/ken/games_old

Notes:

Bind mounts work at kernel level; no symbolic link is needed. Programs see the directory as if it never moved.
/var must mount before any bind mount references in fstab (already satisfied here).
