NVIDIA Driver & CUDA Post-Mortem (Akuma)
Hardware / Kernel Context
GPU: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060
Kernel: 6.18.20-1-cachyos-lts (64-bit)
OS: CachyOS Linux (Arch-based, fast-moving rolling updates)
Reason for difficulty:
Latest NVIDIA drivers often fail to compile on this kernel.
Dependencies between driver, kernel headers, and CUDA versions are very strict.
Trial-and-error was required to find a combination that compiled and persisted after reboot.
Working Versions (Pinned)
Component	Version	Location / Notes
NVIDIA Driver	580.142	/usr/lib/nvidia/ and /etc/modprobe.d/ configs
CUDA Toolkit	13.0	/usr/local/cuda-13.0/
cuDNN	8.x (matching 13.0)	Installed under CUDA path

This specific combination works; newer driver/CUDA failed on this kernel during initial testing.

Commands Executed to Install (Verified Working)
# Step 1: Remove any previous failed installations
sudo pacman -Rns nvidia nvidia-utils nvidia-settings nvidia-dkms

# Step 2: Install pinned driver (580.142) and utilities
sudo pacman -S nvidia-580xx nvidia-580xx-utils nvidia-settings

# Step 3: Install matching CUDA
sudo pacman -S cuda-13.0

# Step 4: Verify driver is loaded
nvidia-smi

# Step 5: Optional: configure persistence mode (keeps GPU initialized for AI workloads)
sudo nvidia-smi -pm 1
